## The Transition Mindset

This isn't a career change — it's a career extension. Everything you know about systems, APIs, distributed computing, and debugging still applies. You're adding a new layer on top.

> "I had to, once again in my career, get out of my comfort zone and adapt to the demands of the industry." — Zahere

## What Transfers Directly

- **System design** → Agent architecture
- **API integration** → Tool use and MCP servers
- **Distributed systems** → Multi-agent orchestration
- **Debugging** → Agent tracing and observability
- **Automation** → Agentic workflows

## Month 1 — GenAI Fundamentals

- LLM APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Gemini)
- Prompt engineering and structured outputs
- Embeddings and vector databases
- RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)
- Build: A document Q&A system

## Month 2 — Agent Frameworks

- LangChain and LangGraph
- Tool use and function calling
- Agent memory patterns
- Multi-step reasoning (ReAct, CoT)
- Build: A research agent with web search

## Month 3 — Production Skills

- MLOps fundamentals (not ML training — deployment)
- LLM observability (LangSmith, Langfuse)
- Evaluation and testing LLM outputs
- Cost optimization (caching, model routing)
- Build: A production-ready agent with monitoring

## Key Insight

Don't try to master everything at once. Pick one framework (LangGraph), one LLM provider (Anthropic or OpenAI), and go deep. Breadth comes later.
